title.narrative: Fisheries Integration of Society and Habitats (FISH)

description.narrative: (Malawi): FISH will invest $1,552,570 to improve fisheries biodiversity conservation in four freshwater ecosystems in southern Malawi. ..FY2017 investments will strengthen engagement of district and local institutions in participatory fisheries management to advocate for sustainable fisheries governance; build the capacity of the Malawi College of Fisheries to train extension staff in sustainable fisheries co-management; and promote tree planting, vegetative propagation, and natural regeneration to rehabilitate degraded catchment areas and rivers in order to improve aquatic ecosystems functions related to fish breeding and nursing. ..These activities will help to reduce overfishing and threats to fisheries habitats in these freshwater ecosystems, and place more than 250,000 hectares of biologically significant area under improved natural resource management.
